## 1. Purpose and Scope

This guide establishes a consistent, repeatable protocol for every team member using Claude Enterprise. The same pattern applies whether you are working on RiskMind, QueryMind, MSTR Admin, or any other subject area. Follow it on Day 1 — and it pays dividends on Day 100.

### Core Objectives

- Minimize token consumption without sacrificing quality
- Maintain continuity across sessions and team members
- Keep every Project lean, focused, and easy to hand off
- Apply one standard naming convention across all Projects

-----

## 2. Project Structure Standard

Every Claude Enterprise Project you create should follow this folder and file structure. It is the same pattern regardless of subject area.

### 2.1 Project Naming Convention

```
Format:  [AREA]_[TOPIC]_[ENV]

Examples:
  MSTR_AdminAgent_PROD
  RISKMIND_Underwriting_DEV
  QUERYMIND_NL2SQL_UAT
  DBX_UnityC_Migration_PROD
```

### 2.2 Files to Upload into Every Project Knowledge Base

|File Name              |Contents                                    |Update Frequency           |
|-----------------------|--------------------------------------------|---------------------------|
|`00_PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`|Stack, architecture overview, key decisions |When major decisions change|
|`01_CONVENTIONS.md`    |Coding standards, naming rules, API patterns|When standards evolve      |
|`02_DOMAIN_GLOSSARY.md`|Business domain terms and definitions       |Monthly or as needed       |
|`03_SESSION_LOG.md`    |Cumulative session summaries (rolling)      |After every work session   |
|`04_OPEN_ITEMS.md`     |Open questions, blockers, next steps        |After every work session   |


> **Key Rule:** Files 00, 01, 02 are STABLE — update rarely. Files 03 and 04 are DYNAMIC — update after every session. Claude reads all of them automatically at the start of each chat inside the Project.

### 2.3 Project System Prompt Template

Set this as the Project Instruction (system prompt) when creating the Project. Customize the bracketed sections.

```
You are assisting a Principal Data Engineer and AI Architect.
Stack: [e.g. AWS Bedrock, Databricks, MicroStrategy, Python, FastAPI]
Domain: [e.g. Commercial Insurance / Underwriting]

Always assume:
- Expert-level Python and data engineering knowledge
- No need to explain basics or add disclaimers
- Use requests.Session() for all MSTR REST API calls
- Code output preferred over prose unless asked otherwise
- Reference 03_SESSION_LOG.md for prior session context
- Reference 04_OPEN_ITEMS.md for current open questions
```

