## 3. Daily Session Protocol

Follow this sequence every working day. It takes less than 5 minutes and saves hours of re-explaining context over time.

### 3.1 Opening a New Chat Session

#### Step 1 — Paste your Context Card

Always start a **new chat** (never continue a stale long thread) with a compact context card. Template:

```
## Session Context
Project   : [Project Name]
Date      : [YYYY-MM-DD]
Session # : [e.g. Day 7 / Session 12]
Focus     : [One sentence — what are you doing today]
Ref files : 03_SESSION_LOG.md, 04_OPEN_ITEMS.md
Last done : [2-3 words from last session]
Today goal: [2-3 words of today's goal]
Output    : [code only | explain | draft doc | review]
```

> **Why this matters:** This card costs ~100 tokens. Re-reading a 30-turn old conversation costs 3,000–8,000 tokens. The card is always cheaper.

### 3.2 During the Session

- Start a new chat for each distinct subtask — do not chain unrelated questions in one thread
- Paste only the relevant code section, not full files
- After 2–3 iterations on the same code block, start fresh — old versions burn tokens silently
- Say `code only` or `no explanation` when you just want output
- Around turn 15–20 you will hit context bloat — wrap up and compress before continuing

### 3.3 Closing a Session — The Summary Protocol

Before ending any productive session, always run the **End-of-Session Summary Prompt**:

```
End of session. Please produce a compact handoff summary in this format:

SESSION SUMMARY — [Project Name] — [YYYY-MM-DD]
=================================================
DECISIONS MADE:
  - [decision 1]
  - [decision 2]

CODE / ARTIFACTS PRODUCED:
  - [file or function name] — [one line description]

OPEN QUESTIONS:
  - [question 1]

NEXT SESSION START POINT:
  - [exactly where to pick up]

Keep the entire summary under 30 lines.
```

**After you get the summary:**

1. Copy it and append it to `03_SESSION_LOG.md` in your Project knowledge base
1. Update `04_OPEN_ITEMS.md` with any new open questions
1. Re-upload both files to the Project (replace the old versions)

