## 5. Token Efficiency Rules — Quick Reference

|Situation                     |Wrong Approach                |Right Approach                   |
|------------------------------|------------------------------|---------------------------------|
|Starting a new day’s work     |Reopen yesterday’s chat thread|New chat + Context Card paste    |
|Fixing code repeatedly        |Keep iterating in same thread |Start fresh after 2–3 iterations |
|Explaining your stack         |Re-type it every session      |Put it in `00_PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`|
|Long conversation getting slow|Keep going                    |Summarize → save → new chat      |
|Pasting code for review       |Paste entire 300-line file    |Paste only the relevant function |
|Need code output              |Ask normally                  |Add `code only, no explanation`  |
|Cross-project work            |Mix topics in one chat        |Separate chat per subject area   |
|Resuming after 5+ days away   |Start from scratch            |Read `03_SESSION_LOG.md` first   |

