## 7. Team Sharing and Access Model

|Role                   |Permission Level|Can Do                                          |
|-----------------------|----------------|------------------------------------------------|
|Project Owner / Lead   |Can Edit        |Upload docs, change instructions, manage members|
|Team Member (Developer)|Can Use         |Chat inside project, read all docs, cannot edit |
|Reviewer / Stakeholder |Can Use         |Read-only view, can chat but not modify         |


> **Governance Rule:** Only the Project Owner updates `03_SESSION_LOG.md` and `04_OPEN_ITEMS.md`. Team members send their session summaries to the owner to consolidate. This prevents file conflicts and keeps the knowledge base clean.

**How to share a Project:**

1. Open the Project in Claude.ai
1. Click **Share project** button next to the project name
1. Add members by name or email, or paste a list for bulk invite
1. Assign **Can use** or **Can edit** per person
1. Alternatively set visibility to **Public** so everyone in the org can find it

> Note: Even on a Public project, each person’s individual chat conversations remain private. Only the knowledge base (uploaded files) and instructions are shared.

